Common Commands in dplyr / tidyverse:-
| Function         | Package | Purpose                         | Example                                                         |
| ---------------- | ------- | ------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `filter()`       | dplyr   | Select rows based on conditions | `filter(flights, dep_delay > 60)`                               |
| `select()`       | dplyr   | Select specific columns         | `select(flights, year, month, day)`                             |
| `arrange()`      | dplyr   | Sort rows                       | `arrange(flights, dep_delay)`                                   |
| `mutate()`       | dplyr   | Create new variables            | `mutate(flights, gain = arr_delay - dep_delay)`                 |
| `summarise()`    | dplyr   | Create summary statistics       | `summarise(flights, avg_delay = mean(dep_delay, na.rm = TRUE))` |
| `group_by()`     | dplyr   | Group data for summaries        | `group_by(flights, carrier)`                                    |
| `distinct()`     | dplyr   | Remove duplicate rows           | `distinct(flights, carrier)`                                    |
| `rename()`       | dplyr   | Rename columns                  | `rename(flights, airline = carrier)`                            |
| `slice()`        | dplyr   | Select rows by position         | `slice(flights, 1:10)`                                          |
| `count()`        | dplyr   | Count occurrences               | `count(flights, carrier)`                                       |
| `left_join()`    | dplyr   | Join two datasets               | `left_join(flights, airlines, by="carrier")`                    |
| `right_join()`   | dplyr   | Keep rows from right table      | `right_join(flights, airlines, by="carrier")`                   |
| `inner_join()`   | dplyr   | Keep matching rows only         | `inner_join(flights, airlines, by="carrier")`                   |
| `full_join()`    | dplyr   | Keep all rows from both tables  | `full_join(flights, airlines, by="carrier")`                    |
| `pull()`         | dplyr   | Extract a column as a vector    | `pull(flights, dep_delay)`                                      |
| `glimpse()`      | dplyr   | Quick structure of data         | `glimpse(flights)`                                              |
| `tibble()`       | tibble  | Create modern dataframe         | `tibble(x=1:5, y=6:10)`                                         |
| `pivot_longer()` | tidyr   | Convert wide → long format      | `pivot_longer(data, cols=a:c)`                                  |
| `pivot_wider()`  | tidyr   | Convert long → wide format      | `pivot_wider(data)`                                             |

Example Workflow Using dplyr:-
library(dplyr)

flights %>%
  filter(dep_delay > 60) %>%
  group_by(carrier) %>%
  summarise(avg_delay = mean(dep_delay, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  arrange(desc(avg_delay))

##The operator %>% (pipe) from tidyverse passes results from one step to the next, making code easier to read.

