#Complete List of Tidyverse / dplyr Commands
| Function         | Package  | Purpose                        | Example                                                 |
| ---------------- | -------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| `filter()`       | dplyr    | Select rows based on condition | `filter(flights, dep_delay > 30)`                       |
| `select()`       | dplyr    | Choose specific columns        | `select(flights, year, month, day)`                     |
| `arrange()`      | dplyr    | Sort rows                      | `arrange(flights, dep_delay)`                           |
| `mutate()`       | dplyr    | Create new variables           | `mutate(flights, speed = distance/air_time*60)`         |
| `summarise()`    | dplyr    | Calculate summary statistics   | `summarise(flights, avg = mean(dep_delay, na.rm=TRUE))` |
| `group_by()`     | dplyr    | Group dataset                  | `group_by(flights, carrier)`                            |
| `ungroup()`      | dplyr    | Remove grouping                | `ungroup(flights)`                                      |
| `distinct()`     | dplyr    | Remove duplicate rows          | `distinct(flights, carrier)`                            |
| `rename()`       | dplyr    | Rename columns                 | `rename(flights, airline = carrier)`                    |
| `relocate()`     | dplyr    | Move columns                   | `relocate(flights, carrier, .before = flight)`          |
| `slice()`        | dplyr    | Select rows by index           | `slice(flights, 1:10)`                                  |
| `slice_head()`   | dplyr    | First rows                     | `slice_head(flights, n=5)`                              |
| `slice_tail()`   | dplyr    | Last rows                      | `slice_tail(flights, n=5)`                              |
| `slice_sample()` | dplyr    | Random rows                    | `slice_sample(flights, n=10)`                           |
| `count()`        | dplyr    | Count observations             | `count(flights, carrier)`                               |
| `add_count()`    | dplyr    | Add count column               | `add_count(flights, carrier)`                           |
| `pull()`         | dplyr    | Extract column as vector       | `pull(flights, dep_delay)`                              |
| `glimpse()`      | dplyr    | View structure                 | `glimpse(flights)`                                      |
| `%>%`            | magrittr | Pipe operator                  | `data %>% filter(x>5)`                                  |
| `case_when()`    | dplyr    | Multiple conditions            | `case_when(dep_delay>60 ~ "Late")`                      |
| `if_else()`      | dplyr    | Conditional variable           | `if_else(dep_delay>0,"Late","OnTime")`                  |
| `across()`       | dplyr    | Apply function to many columns | `summarise(across(where(is.numeric), mean))`            |
| `between()`      | dplyr    | Value within range             | `filter(flights, between(dep_delay,10,30))`             |
| `near()`         | dplyr    | Compare floating numbers       | `filter(data, near(x,10))`                              |

#Join Functions
| Function       | Purpose                        | Example                                       |
| -------------- | ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------- |
| `left_join()`  | Keep all rows from left table  | `left_join(flights, airlines, by="carrier")`  |
| `right_join()` | Keep all rows from right table | `right_join(flights, airlines, by="carrier")` |
| `inner_join()` | Keep matching rows only        | `inner_join(flights, airlines, by="carrier")` |
| `full_join()`  | Keep all rows from both tables | `full_join(flights, airlines, by="carrier")`  |
| `semi_join()`  | Rows in x that match y         | `semi_join(flights, airlines)`                |
| `anti_join()`  | Rows in x not in y             | `anti_join(flights, airlines)`                |

#Tidyr (Data Reshaping)

| Function         | Purpose               | Example                                |
| ---------------- | --------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| `pivot_longer()` | Wide → long format    | `pivot_longer(data, cols=a:c)`         |
| `pivot_wider()`  | Long → wide format    | `pivot_wider(data)`                    |
| `separate()`     | Split column          | `separate(data, col, into=c("a","b"))` |
| `unite()`        | Combine columns       | `unite(data, new, a, b)`               |
| `drop_na()`      | Remove missing values | `drop_na(data)`                        |
| `replace_na()`   | Replace NA values     | `replace_na(list(x=0))`                |
| `fill()`         | Fill missing values   | `fill(data, x)`                        |

